<page api="js">
    <shortlink>ux component getConnectionType Method</shortlink>
    <topic>{dialog.object}.getConnectionType Method</topic>

    <description>Returns the type of connection the device has. (May not return reliable information if not running in a PhoneGap shell).</description>
    <syntax>{dialog.Object}.getConnectionType()</syntax>
    <discussion>Possible return values are: 'none', 'connected_unknowntype', 'ethernet', 'wifi', '2g', '3g', '4g', and 'genericcell'.</discussion>
    <note>For Android be sure to include the 'Connection' or 'Network information' plugin.</note>
    
    <example><![CDATA[var connectionType = {dialog.Object}.getConnectionType();]]></example>
    
    <see>
        <ref link="Dialog Component">{dialog.object}</ref>
    </see>

        <terms>ux component,mobile app,phonegap</terms>
</page> 